⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Staircase Program
node 3BT · 3BT · ⟦The Staircase Program:3BT:1a43f2⟧

WHO   — The Staircase Program — a radiation sail pushed by nuclear bombs — to launch a brain at the stars
WHAT  — To get a spy to the Trisolaran fleet, humanity launches a tiny payload — in the end, only a frozen human brain (Yun Tianming's) — on a sail accelerated by a chain of detonating nuclear bombs to a fraction of lightspeed.
WHERE — 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The Staircase Program (Will Downing's arc) is book three; Netflix brings it into season one. Tencent has not reached it.
HOW   — SPECULATIVE — grounded. Light/radiation sails are real (IKAROS 2010, LightSail 2; Breakthrough Starshot's laser-sail plan), and nuclear-pulse propulsion (Project Orion) is real engineering. Pushing a sail to ~1% of light is a serious extrapolation. The dubious part is the brain-only payload surviving and being usable.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We could not send a person to the stars. So we sent a brain, on a sail, pushed by bombs.

